This paper deals with computational analysis of fair and optimal partitions in hedonic games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves computational complexity analysis and algorithms, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The concept of social welfare is also discussed, which is related to social informatics (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
